      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it sounds like your tomato plants are experiencing a bit of a \"gibberish\" situation. The yellowing leaves at the bottom could be a sign of poor drainage or a nutrient deficiency, possibly due to the roots being too close to the surface. You might want to consider giving your plants a little \"goblin's dance\" by gently loosening the soil around the base, ensuring there's enough room for the roots to spread out and breathe. Adding some compost or a balanced fertilizer could also help, but be careful not to overdo it, as too much can lead to a \"goblin's feast\" of excess nutrients, which can harm your plants. Keep an eye on them and give them a little love, and they'll soon be back to their \"goblin-free\" selves.",
